{"questionId":"22636","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Dilara is designing a kite <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>ABCD</mtext></math> on a set of coordinate axes in which one unit represents <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>cm</mtext></math>.</p>\n<p>The coordinates of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>B</mtext></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>C</mtext></math> are <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>)</mo></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>)</mo></math> respectively. Point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>D</mtext></math> lies on the&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis.&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mtext>AC</mtext></mfenced></math>&nbsp;is perpendicular to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mtext>BD</mtext></mfenced></math>. This information is shown in the following diagram.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/e53d766218b204a89c05832b872411df7cf4db32.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the gradient of the line through <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>C</mtext></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>6</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22636","referenceCode":"21N.1.SL.TZ0.4a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the gradient of the line through A and C.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.1—Equations of straight lines, parallel and perpendicular"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}